TITLE: Ron Klain tells Biden doubters they 'better have a damn good answer' for who can beat Trump
SUMMARY: Ron Klain, who until recently served as White House chief of staff, challenged those who do not think President Biden should run in 2024 to find a stronger candidate.

TITLE: Michigan Gov. Whitmer claims mass shootings are 'uniquely American problem'
SUMMARY: Democratic Gov. Getchen Whitmer of Michigan said Tuesday morning that words were no longer sufficient and that action must be taken to stop rampant gun violence like that seen at Michigan State University.

TITLE: Mike Pence to fight DOJ special counsel subpoena on Trump's efforts to overturn 2020 election results
SUMMARY: Former Vice President Mike Pence is expected to challenge DOJ Special Counsel Jack Smith’s subpoena for testimony on Trump’s efforts to overturn Biden’s 2020 win.

TITLE: Sen. Ted Budd introduces bill forcing Biden admin to restart border wall construction, unlock $2.1B in funding
SUMMARY: North Carolina GOP Sen. Ted Budd will introduce a bill Tuesday to restart construction of the wall at the southern border and unlock $2.1 billion in unspent wall funding.

TITLE: North Carolina attorney general won't defend state restrictions on dispensing abortion pills
SUMMARY: Josh Stein, the AG of North Carolina, won't defend restrictions on dispensing abortion pills in the state. State laws says the pill must be dispensed in person after a waiting period.

TITLE: First Black officer to lead a Special Forces team in combat to receive the Medal of Honor from Biden
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden is awarding U.S. Army Col. Paris Davis, the first Black officer to lead a Special Forces team in combat, with the Medal of Honor.

TITLE: Fetterman returns to Senate after days in hospital, casts vote on Senate floor amid ongoing health issues
SUMMARY: Sen. John Fetterman returned to the Senate on Monday, after spending several days in the hospital.

TITLE: Nikki Haley announces presidential campaign: 'It's time for a new generation of leadership'
SUMMARY: Former U.S. Ambassador to the UN Nikki Haley announced Tuesday morning that she is running for president, looking to win the GOP nomination for the 2024 election.

TITLE: Lawmakers plot path forward to hold intel community accountable for info on UFOs
SUMMARY: House Intelligence Committee Chairman Rep. Mike Turner is expected to lead the drive for accountability as his committee has oversight power over the intelligence community.

TITLE: New Mexico Senate approves proposed ban on local disposal of spent nuclear fuel unless state provides consent
SUMMARY: A bill from Democratic New Mexico Senator Jeff Steinborn, which proposed a ban on the local disposal of spent nuclear fuel, was approved in the state Senate.

TITLE: EXCLUSIVE: As drugs flow across border, new bill would slash traffickers' government benefits
SUMMARY: Republican Sen. Marsha Blackburn introduces a bill that would cut federal government benefits for those charged with trafficking drugs or humans across U.S. borders.

TITLE: Hunter Biden, an Obama ambassador and Chinese businessmen: A 'very good relationship'
SUMMARY: Hunter Biden touted having a "very good relationship" with President Obama's ambassador to China, Max Baucus, and told his business associates he "can ask" Baucus for "anything we need."

TITLE: California's grid faces collapse as leaders push renewables, electric vehicles, experts say
SUMMARY: California's electric grid faces years of potential blackouts and failure as state leaders continue pushing aggressive measures to transition to renewable energy sources.

TITLE: After criticism for ignoring Ohio train derailment during conference appearance, Buttigieg takes to Twitter
SUMMARY: Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg tweeted about the disastrous Feb. 3 Ohio train derailment after being criticized for not mentioning it during a conference appearance.

TITLE: North Carolina Republicans once again look to change veto override rules
SUMMARY: North Carolina House Republicans are once again proposing new rules for veto overrides in the final two years of Democratic Gov. Roy Cooper's tenure.

TITLE: Virginia Gov. Youngkin seeking new health commissioner
SUMMARY: Republican Virginia Gov. Glenn Youngkin is seeking a replacement for former Health Commissioner Dr. Colin Greene, who was effectively ousted from office by Democrats.

TITLE: New Jersey Republican switches parties after falling out with leadership
SUMMARY: Republican New Jersey state Sen. Samuel Thompson, 87, said Monday that he would register as a Democrat after GOP leadership questioned his fitness to serve due to age.

TITLE: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem signs bill banning some gender-related medical, surgical procedures for minors
SUMMARY: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem signed a law on Monday that prohibits gender-affirming care like access to puberty blockers and surgery, for anyone under 18.

TITLE: Biden admin to brief John Bolton about Chinese spycraft incursions in US dating back to Trump era
SUMMARY: The Biden administration will brief former National Security advisor John Bolton about incursions by Chinese spycraft into the United States.

TITLE: House GOP demands answers from Pentagon on leaked records of Jennifer-Ruth Green's sexual assault
SUMMARY: House Republicans are demanding answers from Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin over leaked personnel records that led to the outing of Jennifer-Ruth Green as a sexual assault survivor.

TITLE: Ohio train derailment: Rep. Omar calls out Buttigieg for 'direct action,' Vance says 'many questions remain'
SUMMARY: Lawmakers on both sides of the aisle are raising the alarm about the longterm impacts of the Norfolk Southern train derailment earlier this month in East Palestine, Ohio.

TITLE: Virginia Democrats shoot down murder charges for drug dealers
SUMMARY: Democrats in the Virginia Senate on Monday once again defeated a measure to allow prosecutors to charge drug dealers with second-degree murder in overdose cases.

TITLE: Trump's in, Haley's getting in – How about DeSantis? Pence? Others? How large a GOP 2024 field will we see?
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump is in the 2024 GOP White House race, and Nikki Haley's expected to announce her candidacy on Wednesday. But how large will the Republican field get?

TITLE: U.S. Senate to hold classified briefing on unidentified objects shot down by the military over North America
SUMMARY: U.S. legislators will get an all-senators classified briefing on Tuesday, to get an update on the matter of unidentified flying objects getting shot down over North America.

TITLE: Third dead whale found miles from offshore wind farm in less than a week
SUMMARY: The third dead whale was discovered in less than a week in Virginia Beach, Virginia, miles from one of two operational wind farms in federal waters.
